## Next Steps — Review Chaining

**Suggest /plan-design-review** if UI changes (frontend components, CSS, views, user-facing flows) and no design review run. Flag stale reviews (commit hash drift).

**Mention /plan-ceo-review** (soft, not a push) only if: new user-facing features, product direction change, or substantial scope expansion — AND no CEO review exists.

**Flag stale reviews** if eng review found contradicting assumptions.

**No additional reviews needed** → "All relevant reviews complete. Run /ship when ready."

AskUserQuestion:
- **A)** Run /plan-design-review (if UI scope)
- **B)** Run /plan-ceo-review (if significant product change)
- **C)** Ready to implement — run /ship when done

## Unresolved decisions
"Unresolved decisions that may bite you later." Never silently default.
